</taxonomicName>
: A — proboscis, {; B — hooks of a longitudinal row, {; C — egg; D — hooks of a longitudinal row, {.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BE519783E423C699EA4F893F392F8D8" blockId="8.[166,1224,1798,1847]" pageId="8" pageNumber="203">
Рис. 4. 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A62FB3E423C699EECF893F399F8F3" authorityName="Van Cleave" authorityYear="1924" baseAuthorityName="Kaiser" baseAuthorityYear="1893" box="[238,475,1798,1820]" class="Palaeacanthocephala" family="Centrorhynchidae" genus="Centrorhynchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polymorphida" pageId="8" pageNumber="203" phylum="Acanthocephala" rank="species" species="spinosus">
<emphasis id="B92EC56A3E423C699EECF893F399F8F3" box="[238,475,1798,1820]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="203">Centrorhynchus spinosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
от 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A62FB3E423C699FFDF893F0E8F8F3" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[511,682,1798,1820]" class="Aves" family="Falconidae" genus="Falco" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Accipitriformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="203" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tinnunculus">
